            "headline": "Curve Finance records massive $35B trading volume in Q1 2025, up 13% from last year. Over 5.5M transactions made. Total value locked at $1.8B.",
            "id": "8e1b5ee0-18ac-46c3-8ddc-3a1713088709",
            "is_major": false,
            "source": "Cointelegraph",
            "source_type": "news",
            "summary": "Curve Finance, a decentralized lending protocol and exchange, reported record trading volumes of nearly $35 billion in Q1 of 2025, a 13% increase from the same period in 2024, with transactions surging from 1.8 million to 5.5 million. This growth is significant amidst a 20% drop in the cryptocurrency market capitalization in the year to March 31. Curve is adapting to the DeFi landscape, introducing crvUSD stablecoin in June 2024 and forming partnerships to broaden its offerings. CEO Michael Egorov anticipates DEXs evolving into bespoke platforms for stablecoins. Despite these achievements, Curve's TVL is at $1.8 billion, down from $2.5 billion, and its native token, CRV, has faced over a 40% decline in market capitalization in 2025.",
